---
project: grani-memoir
audience:
  - Family (primary — the descendants this memoir is written for)
  - The subject herself, while living (secondary)
hard_rules:
  - Every reconstructed quote and every checkable factual claim traces to a
    row in that chapter's provenance.md — cut the claim or mark it NOT_FOUND
    rather than invent a source.
  - Narrator framing prose stays in the author's own voice; reconstructed
    dialogue stays in the speaker's own recorded cadence. Never conflate
    the two within a scene.
  - AUDITED is the terminal state for every chapter — no chapter ships
    without a clean corpus-audit pass when the corpus tier is active.
# Dual-corpus provenance (issue #597) — declared ONCE at the project level,
# NOT per chapter. anvil/lib/project_brief.py::resolve_corpus_dirs already
# resolves a list of N declared directories, in declared order.
corpus:
  - transcripts/
  - letters/
# Dual voice tiers (issue #461 author tier + issue #598 subject tier) —
# also declared ONCE at the project level. Both tiers are independently
# activated and may coexist: the author tier grounds narrator framing
# prose; subjects ground reconstructed dialogue.
voice:
  style_guide: STYLE_GUIDE.md
  values: VALUES.md
  subjects:
    - name: grani
      corpus: transcripts/grani/**/*.md
      voice_doc: planning/grani-voice.md
    - name: aunt-jo
      corpus: transcripts/aunt-jo/**/*.md
# Optional: the manifest.json anvil:project-photos emits (SKILL.md
# §Photo-placement contract). Absent -> memoir-figures reports "no
# manifest.json resolved" for any \famphoto/\fullphoto/\marginphoto call
# and skips photo resolution (diagrams + PDF still render).
photos: manifest.json
documents:
  - slug: 00-introduction
    artifact_type: memoir
  - slug: 01-childhood
    artifact_type: memoir
  - slug: appendix
    artifact_type: memoir
---

# Grani memoir — project brief

A family memoir narrated by the author's grandmother's grandson, reconstructing
scenes and dialogue from interview transcripts and collected family letters.
Each chapter is its own thread under `anvil:memoir`; the corpus and voice
tiers above are resolved once at this project level and inherited by every
chapter.

## Reference material

- `transcripts/` — the declared corpus root for interview material (the
  `corpus:` list above).
- `letters/` — the declared corpus root for the collected family letters.
- `research/` — optional shared background (dates, places, historical
  context) that is NOT itself corpus ground truth but may inform framing.

## Assembling the book

This project's chapters are assembled into `book.pdf` via
`/anvil:project-book <project-dir>` — see SKILL.md §"Relationship to
`anvil:project-book`". Do not look for a portfolio command inside
`anvil:memoir` itself.
